TY  - JOUR
AU  - Huang, Jennifer
T1  - Taxable and Tax-Deferred Investing: A Tax-Arbitrage Approach
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn064
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 21
IS  - 5
SP  - 2173
EP  - 2207
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We analyze an intertemporal portfolio problem with both taxable and tax-deferred retirement accounts. Using a tax-arbitrage argument, we identify conditions under which the optimal location decision (where to place an asset) is separable from the allocation decision (how much to allocate to each asset). Investors place highly taxed assets in the tax-deferred account to maximize the tax benefit and adjust their taxable portfolios to achieve the optimal risk exposure. We show that the two-account problem can be reduced to a taxable-account-only problem. The results are robust to capital gains tax deferrals, consumption and contribution decisions, and stochastic tax rates.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn064
ER  - 



