TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bae, Gil S.
AU  - Cheon, Youngsoon S.
AU  - Kang, Jun-Koo
T1  - Intragroup Propping: Evidence from the Stock-Price Effects of Earnings Announcements by Korean Business Groups
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn055
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 21
IS  - 5
SP  - 2015
EP  - 2060
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using earnings announcement events made by firms belonging to Korean chaebols, we examine propping within a chaebol. Consistent with the market's ex ante valuation of intragroup propping, we find that the announcement of increased (decreased) earnings by a chaebol-affiliated firm has a positive (negative) effect on the market value of other nonannouncing affiliates. The sensitivity of the change in the market value of nonannouncing affiliates to abnormal returns for the announcing firms is higher if the cash flow right of the announcing firm's controlling shareholder is higher. The sensitivity is also higher if the announcing firm is larger, performs well, and has a higher debt guarantee ratio.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn055
ER  - 



