TY  - JOUR
AU  - Cumming, Douglas
T1  - Contracts and Exits in Venture Capital Finance
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn072
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 21
IS  - 5
SP  - 1947
EP  - 1982
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using a sample of European venture capital (VC) investments, I study the relation between VC contracts and exits. The data indicate that ex ante, stronger VC control rights increase the likelihood that an entrepreneurial firm will exit by an acquisition, rather than through a write-off or an IPO. My findings are robust to controls for a variety of factors, including endogeneity and cases in which the VC preplans the exit at the time of contract choice. My findings are consistent with control-based theories of financial contracting, such as Aghion and Bolton (1992).
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn072
ER  - 



